<br>
Seriously though, isn't there anything they can do to help?<br>
<br>
I know if there has been items going both ways they probably couldn't because then there would be the argument that maybe he just decided later that he didn't like the price or something, but when it's obviously a mistake and the person won't return it, the GM's really can't do anything?  Why?<br>
<br>
Before you start flaming me, yes I realize he messed up by hitting trade, yes I realize that he shouldn't really be doing trades with &quot;switich to a mule&quot; type deals anyway, but be serious, have none of you EVER just handed something to someone and hit trade?  /eye  <br>
<br>
