<br>
Reguardless, it's still wrong to keep something that isn't yours.  People had me things all the time, sometimes I don't even notice it came from someone I don't know right away.  BUT, when Lagingtrader_01 sends me a tell asking if he gave me something, and I check and see that he did, I give it back lol.  Ubbarlewtz is being listed here because he would not give it back and lied about having it.  If I ever do that to someone ( which I never would ), I hope they list me here too.  Yes it's their fault for hitting trade, but it's not their fault that the person who got it has no honor.  <br>
<br>
I can't remember his name at the moment ( but i'd know it if i saw it ), but there was that one guy ( nine realms thing I think, /cheer again NR <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) who admited to taking the stuff and his defense was, well he hit trade so it's his fault.  I just seem to be seeing alot of &quot;well that sucks but you hit trade so it's kind of your fault&quot; posts about this kind of stuff lately.  Yes, he made a mistake, but it's NOT his fault that this ubbarlewtz has no honor.<br>
